The paper presents a framework for short term load forecasting and uses machine learning techniques to analyze observational data from a residential Demand Response program. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of energy systems, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of incentive mechanisms, which could be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with residential energy consumption, which could be relevant to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
